4 Section 8C. There is hereby created in the registry a medical advisory board, consisting
5 of the commissioner of the department of public health or his designee, who shall serve as
6 chairman thereof, and fifteen members appointed by the registrar and approved by said
7 commissioner, who shall be registered under the laws of the commonwealth as qualified
8 physicians, optometrists or chiropractors, but not more than one of said appointees shall be a
9 chiropractor and not more than one of said appointees shall be an optometrist. The members of
